HEADWORD: Indirubin
<hw>In`di*ru"bin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Indi</ets>go + L. <ets>ruber</ets> red.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance isomeric with, and resembling,
indigo blue, and accompanying it as a side product, in its artificial
production.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indiscernible</ent>⟦br⟧
